<br>
JAKE's Porche is idling<br>
Music Cue: Yet Another Movie/Round and Around<br>
<br>
SERIES OF SHOTS<br>
<br>
A BLACK CORVETTE with BLACKED OUT WINDOWS pulls up next to JAKE'S PORSCHE<br>
<br>
JAKE looks at it.<br>
<br>
JAKE looks at the light, still red.<br>
<br>
BLACK CORVETTE races its engine, still in neutral.<br>
<br>
CLOSEUP, JAKE's EYES, darting to the CORVETTE. It's obvious the car wants to race JAKE, and JAKE won't pass up the opportunity.<br>
<br>
CLOSEUP, JAKE's HANDS on the wheel.<br>
<br>
CLOSEUP, the light facing the other way starts to turn yellow.<br>
<br>
CLOSEUP, JAKE's EYES.<br>
<br>
CLOSEUP, other light turns red.<br>
<br>
CLOSEUP, JAKE's light turns green.<br>
<br>
--<br>
<br>
BOTH CARS screech off.<br>
<br>
ACTION SEQUENCE of the two cars going through a DANGEROUS race, blowing lights, just missing trains and people and other cars. ALL during the race, JAKE keeps stealing glances at the other car's progress, which keeps up with him easily. What JAKE doesn't see is that, while JAKE narrowly avoids obstacles, the CORVETTE is PASSING THROUGH THEM, as if they were smoke.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
EXTERIOR: MOUNTAIN ROAD, DAY<br>
<br>
BOTH CARS head up a mountain road, still racing. JAKE is actually starting to sweat now, but still figures he can beat the other car. There is no question in his mind. SUDDENLY, BOTH CARS bump into each other, lose control, and go OVER THE EDGE of the road. They FREEZE in pace, hanging in mid air, twenty feet away from the embankment they shot off of. EVERYTHING, except for JAKE, is frozen in place, as if time has stopped. As a matter of fact, it has.<br>
<br>
The door to the CORVETTE opens, and DEATH steps out.<br>
<br>
You cannot see DEATH's face. He is garbed in traditional reaper's robe, hood concealing everything but two burning eyes. He stands as if on solid ground next to the car. JAKE opens his door, and, looking down only once, steps out and also stands on solid, though invisible, ground. JAKE just stares at DEATH.<br>
<br>
DEATH:<br>
<br>
(In a deep, terrifying voice)<br>
<br>
I...am...Death!<br>
<br>
(NO reaction from JAKE)<br>
<br>
I am DEATH!<br>
<br>
(Nothing from JAKE)<br>
<br>
I am Death, mortal!<br>
<br>
(JAKE just looks at him)<br>
<br>
(In a normal voice)<br>
<br>
You really AREN'T afraid of me, are you?<br>
<br>
(In a flash, DEATH is garbed in a simple black tuxedo. He looks like a normal man, somewhat short, with a trim black goatee. He regards JAKE with an ironic smile)<br>
<br>
Good. Very good.<br>
<br>
(He starts to walk to JAKE)<br>
<br>
I've been waiting to meet someone like you for two thousand years now.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
This isn't happening. This is bad beer.<br>
<br>
<br>
DEATH:<br>
<br>
No, Jake, this is happening. You're too rational a man to accept the irrational, that's all. But if you stop to think about what's happening, you'll realize that this IS happening.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
(after a pause)<br>
So you're Death. So what? What now?<br>
<br>
<br>
DEATH:<br>
<br>
(Taken aback, then suddenly laughing out loud)<br>
THAT'S the spirit! You are more than I had ever dreamed, able to assimilate and accept my presence so quickly. Oh, you'll do VERY well...<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
Well for WHAT? Am I dead? Is this why you're here?<br>
<br>
<br>
DEATH:<br>
<br>
Dead? Oh no, you're not dead. (Gesturing to the car poised in midair) Well, not YET, anyway. And if you and I make a certain...um....agreement....?....then you need not be dead at all....or, at least, not until you are naturally slated for it.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
You mean, you arranged for this to happen? (DEATH nods) <br>
Why?<br>
<br>
<br>
DEATH:<br>
<br>
For what seemed to me to be a one in a million chance. I NEED YOU.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
How?<br>
<br>
<br>
DEATH:<br>
<br>
Ah, a man of many words. Well, you may be short with me now, but I actually heard you in the bar talking to your poor legless friend. The speech about cheating me. Do you remember it?<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
I recall it.<br>
<br>
<br>
DEATH:<br>
<br>
I need someone like you....fearless. Afraid of nothing. Especially...me.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
And I fit the profile.<br>
<br>
<br>
