Of course you're right.<br>
(Thoroughly depressed)<br>
Kane was right. There can't be a God.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Nonsense.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
What god could let things like this happen?<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
What? Not allow you to ruin a young woman's life? A merciful one, I would suppose.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
No. I mean all of this. This whole system. Disease. Accidents. War. Death. You couldn't imagine the things I've seen.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
My boy. You can't imagine the things I'VE seen. You're shocked now, but you are just beginning to open your eyes, and the truth bothers you. From what you've told me about yourself, you've never stared Death right in the face. Sure, you've skirted it and flirted with it, but you were like a shy boy at his first dance, not willing to look into your partner's eyes. I've seen death, plenty of it. It's the natural way of things. And I've learned to accept it, and in turn, understand it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
Everything rots, Kane said. How can you accept that?<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
The best fertilizer is that which has died. We're all fertilizer. We sacrifice our bodies that God has loaned us to help more grow. The soul doesn't die, not if given the proper passage. Who knows what lies beyond that white door? Or the black, for that matter? But it must be SOMETHING worth living and dying for. Why else would it be there? If there wasn't a God, who set UP the whole thing in the first place? I don't know if he's a merciful god, or a terrible god, or both, or just some space alien from Planet X. But I have to believe there is some form of higher being. Otherwise, I believe I would go mad. There has to be some reason for our lives, and for our souls to continue on when our flesh withers. That's called faith, Jake, and it's one of the most powerful forces in the world. It's made religions, started wars, and created miracles. I don't want to live in a world without faith. It would kill any chance of Hope, and hope gave me a reason to wake up every day.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
I understand. My god, you have a better grip on this than I do. I only wish...<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Wish what?<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
I wish there was some way I could touch her. I mean really touch her, touch her face, if only for a second....<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
You could, I imagine. There is a way.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
What?<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Take my body.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
You mean like possess you or something?<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
No. Take my body. Trade with me. I don't fear death. I haven't feared it for years.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
(Finally understanding)<br>
Take your body....<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
You're obviously not cut out for this, while I think I might have find the whole thing rather fascinating. Imagine, after years of studying the occult, to actually EXPERIENCE death from a whole new angle. The only drawback is you'd probably only have a few weeks, tops, in a rather frail old wrinkled body.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
You don't know what I'd give.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
(soft)<br>
Yes, I think I do. And you may have the will I don't to break out of the coma. Are you willing to take that chance?<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
I've been taking risks against death all my life. This time I'll take a risk against LIFE.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Then we'll do it. I must say, I find the prospect exciting.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
The hours suck. (Laughs)<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
(with a wink)<br>
But for me, the perks are worth it.<br>
<br>
<br>
((Suddenly JAKE hears the SONG OF THE DEAD))<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
What's the matter?<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
The Call. I've got to go, one more time. I won't leave anymore ghosts walking around.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Then godspeed, and hurry back. The old body of mine hasn't been feeling up to snuff lately, and I believe time is of the essense for both of us.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
Yes, I'll be right back.<br>
