<br>
The scene switches back and forth.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA on the hospital bed, not moving. The scene shifts to show the passing of time, as his EKG slows down.<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA sleeping, restlessly. Every now and then she sits bolt upright in bed. Once she says &quot;Jake!&quot; but then goes back to sleep, a tear rolling from her closed eye.<br>
<br>
At the end of one of these scenes, she says:<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA:<br>
<br>
Well, it was a beautiful dream....<br>
<br>
then cut to:<br>
<br>
(SYLVIA'S phone ringing. It's DIANE's voice on the other side. SYLVIA wakes up with a start)<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA:<br>
<br>
Hello?<br>
<br>
<br>
DIANE'S VOICE:<br>
<br>
Sylvia, get to the hospital quick....Mr. Somma woke up....<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA:<br>
<br>
What??? He did?<br>
<br>
<br>
DIANE'S VOICE:<br>
<br>
Hurry, he's going fast...<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA:<br>
<br>
What?<br>
<br>
<br>
DIANE'S VOICE:<br>
<br>
He's been asking for you, honey. But he's dying....<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA:<br>
<br>
I'll be right there. Tell him to hold on!<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
INTERIOR: CAB<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA is in the back seat as the cab driver races along.<br>
<br>
SYLVIA:<br>
<br>
Just hold on, Mr. Somma....<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
INTERIOR: SOMMA's HOSPITAL ROOM<br>
<br>
Several doctors are doing doctor things, trying to keep SOMMA holding on. SYLVIA rushes to his side.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
(Holding out hand)<br>
Sylvia....<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA:<br>
<br>
I'm here....you....finally decided nap time was over, huh?<br>
(She takes his hand)<br>
<br>
<br>
((In the background, you hear a nurse say &quot;He's back at normal&quot; and a doctor answer &quot;That was close....&quot;))<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
(irritably to the voices)<br>
Of course I'm alright. Just had a bad moment. Now get out and leave me alone for a minute.<br>
<br>
((Doctors and nurses back off, but don't leave. SOMMA gives them an exasperated look, and turns to SYLVIA))<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA:<br>
<br>
(Near tears)<br>
You're alive! and awake!<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
(whispering, with a smile on his face)<br>
Not for long. But I don't want to waste my last minutes with them.<br>
<br>
<br>
SYLVIA:<br>
<br>
Mr. Somma...<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Shhhh. ....don't cry when I'm gone....I'm going to a higher place. And remember, even if you can't see him, your guardian angel will be watching over you (takes her hand to his lips, kisses the back of it, then her palm...)<br>
<br>
((SOMMA dies))<br>
<br>
((SYLVIA'S eyes well with tears, but are open, amazed, looking at the spot where he kissed her palm, then back to the dead old man in the bed))<br>
<br>
((Behind her stands SOMMA dressed in reaper garb. The SONG of the DEAD is humming. JAKE'S spirit rises out of the dead body on the hospital table.))<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Was it worth it?<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
It was worth it.<br>
<br>
<br>
((SOMMA raises the doors))<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
You know the routine.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
But wait, if you have any questions, you need to ask Kane....<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Oh, I've met Kane already. I had to after your lovely description of him. But he won't be causing anymore trouble with sudden deaths in those woods anymore. I told him if he was VERY good I'd set him free to go through the white door.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
What? You figured out how to DO that?<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
(with a wink)<br>
No. I lied. But HE believed it.<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
It's been a pleasure knowing you. You'll do a better job. I know it.<br>
((Then JAKE'S smile fades))<br>
Now, I should go.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Yes.<br>
<br>
<br>
((JAKE walks towards the doors. He walks up to the black door and pauses in front of it))<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
I know you might not understand this, but this is the only door I could take.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
But why??<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
I was given this job, however much I didn't want it, and I had a responsibility to it. I made mistakes....<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
We all make mistakes....<br>
<br>
<br>
JAKE:<br>
<br>
...and caused a lot of pain for those I loved. Please, don't try to talk me out of this. It's eating me up inside. It's the only choice I can make.<br>
<br>
<br>
((JAKE reaches for the doorknob and tries to turn it)<br>
<br>
((The BLACK DOOR is LOCKED))<br>
<br>
((JAKE spins to face SOMMA))<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
Don't look at ME! <br>
(Then, glancing heavanward, says)<br>
Looks like someone else chose for you....<br>
<br>
<br>
(JAKE looks up for a moment, then turns toward the white door)<br>
<br>
(JAKE opens the white door)<br>
<br>
(JAKE'S body is momentarily washed out by a beautiful white light filling the open doorway)<br>
<br>
(A child's voice is heard laughing from within, just JAKE'S sillouette is seen against the bright white doorway)<br>
<br>
(The shadow of the african BOY appears briefly, reaching up to hold JAKE'S hand, and leads him into the light. The door closes behind him, and disappears)<br>
<br>
<br>
(SOMMA looks at SYLVIA, watching them wheel away his old body. She is crying, but the tears are also full of wonder, as she touches her palm where JAKE had kissed her.)<br>
<br>
((The SONG of the DEAD begins to sing))<br>
<br>
<br>
SOMMA:<br>
<br>
(Pulling up the hood of the reaper garb over his head)<br>
<br>
(To himself<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Come on, Brittlebones. You have a job to do....<br>
<br>
((SOMMA turns, begins walking away slowly with his back to the camera, and slowly fades away))<br>
<br>
<br>
